  "texts": [
    "Network-Based Multi-group Data Integration (NetICS) provides a strategy for integrating diverse group data in tumor gene sequencing (159).",
    "It utilizes network diffusion models on directed functional interaction networks to predict the impacts of genetic, epigenetic, and miRNA variations on downstream genes and proteins.",
    "Multi-omics datasets encompass a wide range of data types and sizes, from gene or metabolite abundances in hundreds of samples to additional dimensions like sample origin and clinical data in single-cell studies, posing the 'curse of dimensionality' (160).",
    "Moreover, the high correlation among variables can introduce multicollinearity, complicating the identification of significant biological markers.",
    "Specific machine learning methods for metabolomics, such as PCA (112), t-SNE (161), and NMF (162), facilitate data reduction and visualization."
  ],
